QueueDefinition.Name: CE_Operations
QueueDefinition.Description: This component queue exposes content extended operations.

OperationDefinition.Name: applySecurityTemplate
OperationDefinition.Description: (Only supported by P8 CE) Applies a security template to a specified document. Note that the object must be associated with a security policy and the specified template must belong to the policy.

OperationDefinition.Name: applySecurityTemplateMany
OperationDefinition.Description: (Only supported by P8 CE) Applies a security template to an array of documents. Note that the objects must be associated with a security policy and the specified template must belong to the policy.

OperationDefinition.Name: cancelCheckout
OperationDefinition.Description: (Only supported by P8 CE) Cancels the checkout of this attachment by deleting the reservation object associated with it.

OperationDefinition.Name: changeClass
OperationDefinition.Description: (Only supported by P8 CE) Changes the class of a specified content object.

OperationDefinition.Name: checkin
OperationDefinition.Description: Checks in a document as a new major version. Completes with ability to specify new content (as a string), and sets property values on the new version. Returns the new version document.

OperationDefinition.Name: checkout
OperationDefinition.Description: Checks out a document from an object store.

OperationDefinition.Name: copy
OperationDefinition.Description: Copies a document or custom object within the same object store and file it to the same folder as the old object if fileToFolder is true. Note that if a document is specified, only the first content element will be copied. Returns the new copy.

OperationDefinition.Name: copyMany
OperationDefinition.Description: Copies an array of documents or custom objects within the same object store and file them to the same folder as the old object if fileToFolder is true. Note that for documents specified, only the first content elements will be copied.

OperationDefinition.Name: createCustomObject
OperationDefinition.Description: (Only supported by P8 CE) Creates a custom object using a specified class, and property values. The object is filed into the specified folder.

OperationDefinition.Name: createDocument
OperationDefinition.Description: Creates a document using a string as its content. The document is filed into the specified folder.

OperationDefinition.Name: createFolder
OperationDefinition.Description: Creates a folder, either at the root of the object store or as a child of the specified folder. Returns the new folder object.

OperationDefinition.Name: delete
OperationDefinition.Description: Deletes the specified object in the object store.

OperationDefinition.Name: deleteMany
OperationDefinition.Description: Deletes an array of objects in the object store.

OperationDefinition.Name: file
OperationDefinition.Description: Adds the specified document to a given folder in the object store.

OperationDefinition.Name: fileMany
OperationDefinition.Description: Files one or more objects (documents or custom objects) into a given folder.

OperationDefinition.Name: getBooleanProperty
OperationDefinition.Description: (Only supported by P8 CE) This method returns a boolean attribute value for the specified property of a content object.

OperationDefinition.Name: getChildDateProperty
OperationDefinition.Description: (Only supported by Content Manager) This method retrieves a Date attribute value for specified attribute name from the specified document or folder in Content Manager.

OperationDefinition.Name: getChildDoubleProperty
OperationDefinition.Description: (Only supported by Content Manager) This method retrieves a Double attribute value for specified attribute name from the specified document or folder in Content Manager.

OperationDefinition.Name: getChildIntegerProperty
OperationDefinition.Description: (Only supported by Content Manager) This method retrieves an Integer attribute value for specified attribute name from the specified document or folder in Content Manager.

OperationDefinition.Name: getChildStringProperty
OperationDefinition.Description: (Only supported by Content Manager) This method retrieves a String attribute value for specified attribute name from the specified document or folder in Content Manager.

OperationDefinition.Name: getContent
OperationDefinition.Description: Returns the content for the specified object in a 3-element string array. Element 1 is filename, 2 is mimeType, and 3 is the content itself.

OperationDefinition.Name: getContentCount
OperationDefinition.Description: Returns the number of content objects for the specified content type (or part type) of the specified document.

OperationDefinition.Name: getContentTypes
OperationDefinition.Description: (Only supported by Content Manager) This method gets the content types (or part types) of the specified document.

OperationDefinition.Name: getContentWithIndex
OperationDefinition.Description: Returns the content based on an index of the total content objects for the specified content type (or part type) of the specified document. The returned content is a 3-element string array. Element 1 is filename, 2 is mimeType, and 3 is the content itself.

OperationDefinition.Name: getDocumentId
OperationDefinition.Description: This method gets a document identifier of the specified attachment.

OperationDefinition.Name: getLatestAttachmentVersion
OperationDefinition.Description: Returns the latest attachment version of the specified attachment.

OperationDefinition.Name: getDateProperty
OperationDefinition.Description: This method returns a date attribute value for the specified property of a content object.

OperationDefinition.Name: getDoubleProperty
OperationDefinition.Description: This method returns a double attribute value for the specified property of a content object.

OperationDefinition.Name: getIntegerProperty
OperationDefinition.Description: This method returns an integer attribute value for the specified property of a content object.

OperationDefinition.Name: getObjectProperty
OperationDefinition.Description: (Only supported by P8 CE) Gets an object attribute value for the specified property of a content object.

OperationDefinition.Name: getObjFromPath
OperationDefinition.Description: (Only supported by P8 CE) Retrieves an object from a specified object store using a specified path (also referred to as containment name). If the object does not exist, an empty attachment will be returned.

OperationDefinition.Name: getMultiBooleanProperty
OperationDefinition.Description: (Only supported by P8 CE) Retrieves the values of a multi-valued boolean property as an array.

OperationDefinition.Name: getMultiChildDateProperty
OperationDefinition.Description: (Only supported by Content Manager) Retrieves a list of Date attribute values for specified attribute name from the specified document or folder in Content Manager.

OperationDefinition.Name: getMultiChildDoubleProperty
OperationDefinition.Description: (Only supported by Content Manager) Retrieves a list of Double attribute values for specified attribute name from the specified document or folder in Content Manager.

OperationDefinition.Name: getMultiChildIntegerProperty
OperationDefinition.Description: (Only supported by Content Manager) Retrieves a list of Integer attribute values for specified attribute name from the specified document or folder in Content Manager.

OperationDefinition.Name: getMultiChildStringProperty
OperationDefinition.Description: (Only supported by Content Manager) Retrieves a list of String attribute values for specified attribute name from the specified document or folder in Content Manager.

OperationDefinition.Name: getMultiDateProperty
OperationDefinition.Description: Retrieves the values of a multi-valued date property as an array.

OperationDefinition.Name: getMultiDoubleProperty
OperationDefinition.Description: Retrieves the values of a multi-valued double property as an array.

OperationDefinition.Name: getMultiIntegerProperty
OperationDefinition.Description: Retrieves the values of a multi-valued integer property as an array.

OperationDefinition.Name: getMultiObjectProperty
OperationDefinition.Description: (Only supported by P8 CE) Retrieves the values of a multi-valued object property as an array.

OperationDefinition.Name: getMultiStringProperty
OperationDefinition.Description: Retrieves the values of a multi-valued string property as an array.

OperationDefinition.Name: getStringProperty
OperationDefinition.Description: This method returns a string attribute value for the specified property of a content object.

OperationDefinition.Name: getURLFromAttachment
OperationDefinition.Description: Returns a URL for the specified attachment.

OperationDefinition.Name: getURLFromAttachmentWithIndex
OperationDefinition.Description: (Only supported by Content Manager) Retrieves the URL of the content based on an index of the total content objects for the specified part type of the specified document.

OperationDefinition.Name: move
OperationDefinition.Description: Moves the specified object from its existing folder to the specified folder. (i.e., unfile and file)

OperationDefinition.Name: moveMany
OperationDefinition.Description: Moves the specified objects from their existing folder to the specified folder (i.e., unfile and file).

OperationDefinition.Name: publish
OperationDefinition.Description: (Only supported by P8 CE) Publishes a source document using the specified publishing template. The target document created from the publishing request is returned. See the documentation for the Document publish method for additional information such as when a valid target document is returned.

OperationDefinition.Name: searchForMany
OperationDefinition.Description: Executes a simple search template or stored search, identified via an attachment. Returns all matching objects as an attachment array.

OperationDefinition.Name: searchForOne
OperationDefinition.Description: Executes a simple search template or stored search, identified via an attachment. Returns the first matching object as an attachment.

OperationDefinition.Name: sendMail
OperationDefinition.Description: Sends mail as text/plain with no attachment.

OperationDefinition.Name: sendMailAttachment
OperationDefinition.Description: Sends mail with a document attachment. The document is added to the email as a MIME attachment.

OperationDefinition.Name: sendMailTemplate
OperationDefinition.Description: Sends mail using a template. The template is used as the body of the email message.

OperationDefinition.Name: sendMailTemplateAttachment
OperationDefinition.Description: Sends mail using a template with a document attachment. The document is added to the email as a MIME attachment.

OperationDefinition.Name: sendMailTemplateURL
OperationDefinition.Description: Sends mail using a template with the URL of the attached documents. The URL are appended to the end of the body of the email.

OperationDefinition.Name: sendMailURL
OperationDefinition.Description: Sends mail with the URL of the attached documents. The URL are appended to the end of the body of the email.

OperationDefinition.Name: setBooleanProperty
OperationDefinition.Description: (Only supported by P8 CE) This method sets a boolean attribute value for the specified property of a content object.

OperationDefinition.Name: setContent
OperationDefinition.Description: (Only supported by Content Manager) This method sets the content of the specified object.

OperationDefinition.Name: setContentWithIndex
OperationDefinition.Description: (Only supported by Content Manager) This method sets the content of the specified object with a specified index.

OperationDefinition.Name: unfile
OperationDefinition.Description: Unfiles the specified object from the specified folder.
